<subSubSection id="74ED0E86FFE6FF82E5D6014532CFFD06" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3C485D0DFFE6FF82E5D6014532CFFD06" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,655]" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E5D601453360FEC6" bold="true" box="[199,328,312,335]" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Discussion:</emphasis>
The species has been previously recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="586620FCFFE6FF82E65701453640FEC6" author="Demircan" box="[838,1128,312,335]" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" refString="Demircan, N. &amp; Topcu, A. (2015) A contribution to the spider fauna of the European part of Turkey (Araneae). Serket, 14 (4), 176 - 183." type="journal article" year="2015">Demircan &amp; Topçu (2015)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E18001453718FEC6" authorityName=": Demircan &amp; Topcu" authorityYear="2015" box="[1169,1328,312,335]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chyzeri">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E18001453718FEC6" box="[1169,1328,312,335]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Textrix chyzeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is obviously a misidentification. It certainly does not belong to 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E63201253144FEE6" box="[803,876,344,367]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E63201253144FEE6" box="[803,876,344,367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Textrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at all because of the notched trochanters (straight in 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E586010532C8FE06" box="[151,224,376,399]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E586010532C8FE06" box="[151,224,376,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Textrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), straight eyerows (recurved in 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E72501053055FE06" box="[564,637,376,399]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E72501053055FE06" box="[564,637,376,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Textrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the presence of a patellar apophysis (missing in 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E1A901053729FE06" box="[1208,1281,376,399]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E1A901053729FE06" box="[1208,1281,376,399]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Textrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Although its genital structure also differs from all known 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E79301E530D9FE26" authorityName="Dimitrov &amp; Deltshev &amp; Lazarov" authorityYear="2017" box="[642,753,408,431]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Histopona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E79301E530D9FE26" box="[642,753,408,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Histopona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the somatic characters (notched trochanters, presence of only dorsal spines on patellae, presence of patellar apophysis) are much closer to this genus (according to 
<bibRefCitation id="586620FCFFE6FF82E1D001C537B9FE46" author="Bolzern" box="[1217,1425,440,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" refString="Bolzern, A., Pantini, P. &amp; Isaia, M. (2013) Revision of the Histopona italica group (Araneae: Agelenidae), with the description of two new species. Zootaxa, 3640 (1), 23 - 40. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3640.1.2" type="journal article" year="2013">
Bolzern 
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E00D01C53779FE46" box="[1308,1361,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E58601A533A4FE66" authority="Dimitrov &amp; Deltshev &amp; Lazarov, 2017" authorityName="Dimitrov &amp; Deltshev &amp; Lazarov" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,396,472,495]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Histopona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviemboli" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E58601A533A4FE66" box="[151,396,472,495]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Histopona breviemboli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15B03C64FFE6FF82E48401A533F8FE66" box="[405,464,472,495]" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
slightly resembles the species of 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E65001A5318FFE66" authorityName="Brignoli" authorityYear="1977" box="[833,935,472,495]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Histopona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="italica">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E65001A5318FFE66" box="[833,935,472,495]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">H. italica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—group by the overall structure of the bulbus and reduced colulus. For the record of 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E751018530F6FD86" authorityName=": Demircan &amp; Topcu" authorityYear="2015" box="[576,734,504,527]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Textrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chyzeri">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E751018530F6FD86" box="[576,734,504,527]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Textrix chyzeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cited above, 
<bibRefCitation id="586620FCFFE6FF82E669018536B1FD86" author="Demircan" box="[888,1177,504,527]" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" refString="Demircan, N. &amp; Topcu, A. (2015) A contribution to the spider fauna of the European part of Turkey (Araneae). Serket, 14 (4), 176 - 183." type="journal article" year="2015">Demircan &amp; Topçu (2015)</bibRefCitation>
provide a picture and a short description of the female. The presented picture of the female epigyne also resembles those of 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E1E902653714FDA6" authorityName="Brignoli" authorityYear="1977" box="[1272,1340,536,559]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Histopona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="italica">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E1E902653714FDA6" box="[1272,1340,536,559]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">italica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—group. However, the embolus of 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E4B8024530B5FDC6" authority="Dimitrov &amp; Deltshev &amp; Lazarov, 2017" authorityName="Dimitrov &amp; Deltshev &amp; Lazarov" authorityYear="2017" box="[425,669,568,591]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Histopona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviemboli" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E4B8024530B5FDC6" box="[425,669,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Histopona breviemboli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="15B03C64FFE6FF82E7B5024530F5FDC6" box="[676,733,568,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is much shorter than in any other 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E1590245369FFDC6" authorityName="Dimitrov &amp; Deltshev &amp; Lazarov" authorityYear="2017" box="[1096,1207,568,591]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Histopona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E1590245369FFDC6" box="[1096,1207,568,591]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Histopona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species and the radix is also very different, having a thorn-like shape, so the species cannot be placed in any of the existing 
<taxonomicName id="FBF7268EFFE6FF82E1C002253768FDE6" authorityName="Dimitrov &amp; Deltshev &amp; Lazarov" authorityYear="2017" box="[1233,1344,600,623]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Histopona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0E83811FFFE6FF82E1C002253768FDE6" box="[1233,1344,600,623]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="286">Histopona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroups.
</paragraph>
